SpiderWebNode<E> - Class in com.spiderweb
The SpiderWebNode class represents a node in the SpiderWeb data structure, where each node stores a value and maintains references to its next and previous nodes, as well as references to nodes on the next and previous levels.
SpiderWebNode(E, SpiderWebNode<E>, SpiderWebNode<E>) - Constructor for class com.spiderweb.SpiderWebNode
Constructs a SpiderWebNode with the specified value, previous node, and previous level node.
